text:
Staves here don't work like in the original games. There are several kind of staves:{br}
Support staves: They can only be used by support classes. Support classes have a staff icon <icon>Staff</> in their description.{br}
Offensive staves. These staves can be used to attack and don't have the support class restriction. Some of these staves will always hit, giving staff users a safer attack option, but they can't crit.

Functioning similarly to Fire Emblem Engage, heavy weapons always attack second and can't double the enemy. Here they're also effective against frozen enemies.{br} 
Like their name suggests, they have a high weight.{br} These weapons will shove the attacked unit.{br}
In general, the heavy versions of weapons are the following:{br}Blades(swords){br}Greatlances(lances){br}Warhammers(axes){br}
Heavy weapons can also come as tomes or bows; they aren't limited to the classic weapon triangle.

Gleipnir does effective damage against monsters. {br}Both the Slim Sword and the Slim Lance give WEXP faster and use Speed in their damage formula. 
Fire magic (not only the Fire tome) is effective against Horse units. {br}
Thunder magic (not only the Thunder tome) is effective against Armor units.{br} 
Light magic and daggers will do extra damage when doing a critical hit. This means that even if a normal hit would do 0 damage, you'll damage the enemy with a critical hit. {br}
Eirika's Rapier has 1-2 range. {br}Sieglinde and Siegmund are also effective against Armor and Horse enemies.
